LC 53: Maximum Subarray

1. Kadane's Algorithm (Index Tracking)
Pattern

Return maximum sum along with subarray indices.

Template
int currentSum = 0;
int maxSum = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

int start = 0;
int end = 0;
int tempStart = 0;

for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {

    currentSum += nums[i];

    if (currentSum > maxSum) {
        maxSum = currentSum;
        start = tempStart;
        end = i;
    }

    if (currentSum < 0) {
        currentSum = 0;
        tempStart = i + 1;
    }
}

// Maximum subarray = nums[start...end]
2. Maximum Product Subarray
Pattern

Track both maximum and minimum products because multiplying by a negative swaps them.

Template
int maxProd = nums[0];
int minProd = nums[0];
int ans = nums[0];

for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {

    if (nums[i] < 0) {
        int temp = maxProd;
        maxProd = minProd;
        minProd = temp;
    }

    maxProd = Math.max(nums[i], maxProd * nums[i]);
    minProd = Math.min(nums[i], minProd * nums[i]);

    ans = Math.max(ans, maxProd);
}

return ans;
